## ğŸ” **Breaking Down the Script**

ğŸ“Œ **Shebang (**`#!/bin/bash`) â€“ Defines the script interpreter.  
ğŸ“Œ **Comments (**`#`) â€“ Used to add explanations.  
ğŸ“Œ **Echo (**`echo "text"`) â€“ Prints messages to the terminal.  
ğŸ“Œ **Variables (**`var=value`) â€“ Stores data.  
ğŸ“Œ **Arithmetic Operations (**`$((expression))`) â€“ Performs calculations.  
ğŸ“Œ **Built-in Variables (**`$USER, $HOME, $PWD, $SHELL, $HOSTNAME, $OSTYPE`) â€“ Displays system info.  
ğŸ“Œ **Wildcards (**`*.txt, script*.sh, [abc]*.sh, ?file.*`) â€“ Lists specific files.

